cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.DC 

This paper proposes a method for addressing the big data challenge in regression problems with closed-form solutions. As such, it is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. 

Firstly, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new learning approach for regression problems. 

Secondly, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses techniques for handling large datasets that cannot be stored in RAM. 

Thirdly, cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of accessing and updating large datasets. 

Fourthly, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a new approach for solving regression problems, which is a common task in AI. 

Finally, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of parallel computing clusters for computing multiple models simultaneously.
